Normal Sudoku rules mostly apply. Digits 0-9 may not repeat within a row, column or box.

Cells with a grey square must contain an even digit.

A 0 in the grid, always gives the coordinates of a 0 (row/column) by the missing 1-9 digits it replaces the given row/column.
A box containing a 0 consists of the same set of digits as the column in which the 0 appears.
The double ring is the total number of 0s in the grid.

Standard Killer cage rules apply, i.e. digits in a cage are unique and sums to the number in the corner, if given. 

All lines are Renban lines, i.e. all the digits along a form a consecutive set of digits.

The Z-line is also a Dutch Whisper line, i.e. neighbouring digits on the line must differ by at least 4 (Dutch Whisper).

The black and white Kropki _squares_ (on lines) indicates that the sum of digits on each segment partitioned by the square must be double and respectively adjacent to one another.
